Installation of the Webmin LTSP module

1. Download the ltsp-0.x.tar.gz package from
   http://termserv.berlios.de/ltsp-module/

2. Unpack the package in your webmin module directory, e.g.
   /usr/share/webmin on Debian or
   /usr/libexec/webmin on Caldera:

   cd <webmin-module-directory>; tar -xzvf <package>

2. Create /etc/webmin/ltsp, mode 711, owner root:root

3. Create an empty file /etc/webmin/ltsp/admin.acl, mode 600, owner root:root

4. Copy /usr/share/webmin/ltsp/config-<your-distribution>-linux to
   /etc/webmin/ltsp/config, mode 600, owner root:root

5. Add ltsp in /etc/webmin/webmin.acl

6. Restart the webmin daemon, e.g.
   /etc/rc.d/init.d/webmin restart on Caldera and most Linuxes or
   /etc/init.d/webmin restart on Debian (not sure)

